## Styling Rules

- **Theme**: Dark-only. Do not add light theme variants unless explicitly required.

- **Tokens**: Use semantic tokens from theme CSS; avoid hardcoded colors. If a new color is needed, add a semantic token rather than inline hex.

- **Tailwind**: Use Tailwind for layout, spacing, typography. Keep class lists concise; avoid deeply nested utility chains.

- **Base components**: `components/ui/*` should remain theme-compliant; avoid per-component hardcoded colors.

- **Global CSS**: Place shared styles in `src/app/globals.css` or `src/app/styles/*`; avoid scattering ad-hoc styles in components.

- **Responsiveness**: Use Tailwind responsive utilities; test key breakpoints.

- **Animations/Transitions**: Keep subtle; prefer CSS utilities defined under `styles/animations.css` when possible.

- **Consistency**: Reuse spacing/typography scale; avoid one-off sizes unless justified.

